Step 1. Calculate the Return on Equity (ROE):  
• Net Profit (from income statement) = –1,175,062.19  
• Owner’s Equity at beginning is given on 2023‑12‑31 as 13,000,000.00, and End Owner’s Equity (2024‑01‑29) is 11,824,937.81.  
• Average Owner’s Equity = (13,000,000.00 + 11,824,937.81) / 2 ≈ 12,412,468.91  
• ROE = (Net Profit ÷ Average Owner’s Equity) = –1,175,062.19 ÷ 12,412,468.91 ≈ –0.0947 → as a percentage: –9.47%

Step 2. Calculate the Debt to Asset Ratio:  
• Total Liabilities are given as “Total Current Liabilities” = 3,054,996.05  
• Total Assets (End amount) = 14,879,933.86  
• Debt to Asset Ratio = 3,054,996.05 ÷ 14,879,933.86 ≈ 0.2053, which rounded to two decimals is 0.21

Step 3. Calculate the Gross Profit Margin:  
• Gross Profit (from income statement) = 1,559,920.95  
• Total Revenue = 7,099,920.95  
• Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit ÷ Total Revenue) = 1,559,920.95 ÷ 7,099,920.95 ≈ 0.22  
• As a percentage, this is 22.00%

Thus, the final answer in the required JSON format is as follows:

{
  "solution": {
    "Return on Equity (ROE)": "-9.47%",
    "Debt to Asset Ratio": "0.21",
    "Gross Profit Margin": "22.00%"
  }
}
